    <h2 id="plant-layout">Used Oil Centrifuge Plant Layout</h2>
    <p>
      For commercial-scale processing, a typical <a href="/used-oil-centrifuge-plant/">6 MGY used oil centrifuge plant</a> uses a <a href="/decanter-centrifuge/">decanter centrifuge</a> for bulk de-sludging followed by a disc stack centrifuge for polishing and water separation. This two-stage approach handles the full range of solids loading — the decanter removes particles up to ¼″ while the disc stack centrifuge polishes down to 0.5 microns.
    </p>
    <p>
      A 6 MGY plant (25 GPM at 5 days/week, 20 hours/day) can be accommodated within a <strong>4,000 sq ft facility</strong>, not including incoming oil storage tanks — a fraction of the footprint required by conventional heating and settling operations. See our <a href="/used-oil-centrifuge-plant/">used oil centrifuge plant layout</a> article for the complete piping diagram, equipment list, and auxiliary equipment specifications.
    </p>

    <h2 id="general-oil-separation">General Oil Separation</h2>
    <p><strong>Versatile Oil Purification</strong> — Beyond motor oil, our centrifuges handle a wide range of petroleum and bio-based oils. Whether you need to purify, clarify, or polish oil at 5–60 GPM, Dolphin has a solution.</p>
    <p>See our full <a href="/oil-centrifuge/">oil centrifuge</a> overview for the complete range of oil separation applications we support.</p>

    <h2 id="choosing-the-right-system">Choosing the Right System</h2>
    <p>The right centrifuge depends on your feedstock, throughput requirements, and end-product specifications. Key factors include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Flow rate</strong> — Match centrifuge capacity to your daily volume</li>
      <li><strong>Contaminant load</strong> — Heavy sludge requires a self-cleaning (DMPX series) bowl design</li>
      <li><strong>Water content</strong> — High water content calls for a 3-phase separator</li>
      <li><strong>End-product spec</strong> — Re-refining demands tighter separation than fuel blending</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Our engineers will help you select and size the right system. <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/">Contact us</a> for a consultation, or call <strong>(248) 522-2573</strong> to speak with a specialist today.</p>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">How does a centrifuge clean used motor oil?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">A disc stack centrifuge processes used motor oil at up to 8,000 G-force, separating water, sludge, wear metals, and carbon particles from the clean oil phase. The three-phase design simultaneously removes both water and solids in a single continuous pass at flow rates of 10–60 GPM, producing clean oil suitable for resale, re-refining, or fuel blending.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">What is the difference between waste oil recovery and re-refining?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">Waste oil recovery (also called re-processing) cleans used oil by removing water and solids, producing a product suitable for fuel blending or industrial heating. Re-refining is a more intensive process that restores used oil to base oil quality suitable for lubricant production. Both processes use disc stack centrifuges, but re-refining requires additional treatment steps.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">Can Dolphin Centrifuge systems process black diesel?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">Yes. Black diesel — a fuel blend made from used motor oil and diesel — contains high carbon and soot concentrations that require centrifugal removal for reuse as burner fuel. Dolphin's disc stack centrifuges are specifically configured for high-carbon-content fuels, removing soot and water at 10–30 GPM.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">What flow rate do I need for a used oil collection business?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">For used oil collectors processing 500–2,000 gallons per day, a centrifuge sized at 15–30 GPM (like the DMPX-042) is typically appropriate. Larger re-refiners processing 5,000+ gallons per day may require multiple units or the DMPX-070. Dolphin Centrifuge engineers will size your system based on your daily volume and desired processing cycle time.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">Does Dolphin Centrifuge supply complete used oil processing systems?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">Yes. Dolphin Centrifuge supplies complete turnkey used oil processing systems including the 3-phase disc stack centrifuge, feed pump, electric or steam heater, pre-strainer, flow controls, sludge tank, and PLC panel. Systems are factory-tested at our Warren, MI facility and shipped ready for field connection.</p>
    </details>

